page.title: 08River Ter
page.content: of long tailed tits which flit through the crack willows. Willow warblers, bull finches, reed warblers, yellow hammers, linnets and kingfishers may also be seen. The river is also lined with a variety of trees such as ash, elder, maple, hazel, spindle, sycamore and elm.Plantlife includes cow parsley , campion, broad leaved dock, dogrose, dead-nettle, hemlock trefoil, goats beard and comfrey. Also under the surface for the fisherman can be found a variety of fish. The bottom feeding gudgeon and stone loach to the more common perch, roach, and bream, not forgetting the voracious pike. The river also has an abundance of eels.
